* Iron Raptor shook her head, it wasn't hard to see that the seats had never been sat in, the meeting had never taken place.*

" No. The meeting isn't over...because it never began."

* She took a second look at the seats to try and direct Prowl to look at them as well, to prove that she was right.
It also meant that no bot had heard, listened to, or was to busy to obey Liono's orders to come to the meeting. A small sigh escaped her lips as she then leaned her back against the wall by the door, what was the point of being third in command when there was no team to lead? The Maximals didn't seem to be a team, just stray individuals with their own schedules to keep. Just like her in a way, she had wanted to be with Prowl when Liono had called. She didn't care what he told her to do, she didn't care if he called up ALL of the Maximals to a meeting...just being with Prowl.
So she couldn't blame them, not for being themselves.
Iron Raptor then looked down at the floor, her features so pleasant only moments before not growing gloomy and overcast.*
